‖   § Definition ⦉⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The equation
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ x^p = 1 ⦉
    ⦉
    has $p$ roots and these are called the $p$ roots of 1.
    † ⦊
      ‖ Future editions will expand. ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ We call the complex numbers which solve this equation the
    ❬$p$th roots of one❭ or the ❬($p$th) roots of unity❭. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ A $n$th root of unity $r ∈ 𝗥$ is ❬primitive❭ if it is
    not an $m$th root of unity for any $m < n$. ⦉
⦉


